    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-30T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-30T09:00:00-05:00" n="519"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4A6/322: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-30T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 30, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. During the general discussion at the specific request of the President I made
                    a brief statement which was well received this morning at the plenary session of
                    the Opium Conference embodying the following principles: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>No plan yet presented is entirely acceptable to the United
                            States.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>The United States is prepared to assist in obtaining any practical
                            means by which limitation of manufacture may be attained.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Stated belief that there should be a limitation of the quantities of
                            raw materials which manufacturers are allowed to use thus automatically
                            limiting products.</item>
                        <pb facs="0772" n="658" xml:id="pg_658"/>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>Import and export certificate system should be applied to all opium
                            and coca leaf derivatives.</item>
                        <label>(5)</label>
                        <item>Governments should account for all imports, manufacture, sales and
                            exports of all raw materials and drugs.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Full copy by open mail.<note n="96" xml:id="d519fn96">For text, see Department of
                        State Conference Series No. 10, p. 6.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
